summary: This document outlines the registration requirements for a sexual offender in the Virgin Islands, detailing the obligations to register and update personal information. It emphasizes the legal consequences of failing to comply with these requirements under both local and federal law.
keyFacts: The document discusses the obligations of a sexual offender to register in the Virgin Islands.
Failure to comply with registration requirements can lead to prosecution under Virgin Islands Code and federal law.
The next registration date mentioned is 03/05/2020.
The document includes penalties for non-compliance, including fines and imprisonment.
There is a mention of a requirement to provide personal information and updates within three business days.
